OL,6,FFor several weeks she had been left
OL,7,Flying, immobile, on a downstairs sofa.
OL,9,F"I've got a problem with the wife,"
OL,10,FMorgan had initially told a call
OL,11,Fhandler. "She looks like something
OL,12,Ffrom a death camp. She can't go on
OL,13,Flike this."
OL,15,F"I'm not supporting this behaviour any
OL,16,Fmore," he added. "It has gone too far."
OL,18,FBoth he and Holyoak claimed in
OL,19,Fevidence they were simply following
OL,20,FMrs Morgan's explicit instructions
OL,21,Fthat no help be sought.
