OL,6,FMorgan said he believed his mother
OL,7,Fwouldn't have accepted help had it
OL,8,Fbeen offered sooner. She "intended to
OL,9,Fend her life", he believed.
OL,11,FHis barrister, Richard English, spoke
OL,12,Fof a tragic case, saying: "My client
OL,13,Fhas lost his wife. My learned friend's
OL,14,Flay client (Holyoak) has lost his
OL,15,Fmother."
OL,17,FHe added of Morgan: "He has not got
OL,18,Fover the loss of his wife. He still
OL,19,Fgrieves for her. He misses his wife
OL,20,Fevery day."
